edu.rit.util.test

Class TestBitSet

  • java.lang.Object
    • edu.rit.util.test.TestBitSet

  • public class TestBitSet
extends Object
    Class TestBitSet is a unit test main program for class BitSet. The program creates two bitsets named a and b. The program reads commands from the standard input. Each command is of the form "a.method(args)" or "b.method(args)". There is no whitespace in the command. The program calls the given method with the given arguments on the given bitset, then prints the state of both bitsets. The command "q" quits the program.

    Usage: java edu.rit.util.test.TestBitSet max
    max = Maximum number of elements in bitsets
